description.2: Captain Zero has started a new chapter in his life... but all Spider-Man can remember are Zero’s days as a patient in the Pleasant Valley Mental Hospital.
description.3: Spider-Man joins Johnny Blaze and Ghost Rider's battle against Hag, Troll and Deathspawn, in an all-out Midtown Melee!
description.7: Featuring the first appearance of The Maestro!  Hulk is flung into the distant future to face his ultimate enemy: himself!  The Hulk is the last super power in a post-apocalyptic Earth, ruling with an iron fist as the wicked Maestro. But summoned from the past by a small band of rebels is perhaps the only being who can stand against him!
description.14: The hunt for Demogoblin heightens as Moon Knight's time runs bare!
description.19: Captain America and the Punisher work together in the thrilling conclusion to their unlikely team-up series!
description.20: Spider-Man starts narrowing in on who he believes is the suspect behind the robotic attacks. But can he find out before the robots take over?
description.21: Spider-Man and Black Cat scramble to uncover the source of the Spider-Slayers. Will all trails lead to Max Young? Peter begins to suspect his parents are imposters- but why?
description.22: The Swordsman reveals that the Gatherers are from a paralle universe just as the Watcher appears with an ominous warning.
description.23: The odds are stacked against our heroes, but that's just how they like it! Witness the epic conclusion to Diamondback's rescue!
description.26: Down in the New York City sewers, Ghost Rider, Johnny Blaze and Venom must work together to find out where Spider-Man has been taken!
description.27: Switching bodies with Weezi proves perilous for She-Hulk!
description.28: It's trial day, and VENOM is called to the stand! When the symbiotic psycho hijacks a courtroom, it's up to Spider-Man and Daredevil to stop him! But can they do it before Venom declares everyone guilty?
description.30: Daredevil! Under the possession of Calypso! The Yves Chapoteau case hits a new complication.
description.31: Trouble on both sides! With both the Crazy Gang and the trolls that kidnapped Alchemy on the loose, can even the combined strength of Excalibur and the X-Men come out on top?
description.33: Hulk is informed of the Leader's whereabouts and makes his pursuit in a stampede of rage. But the Green Giant isn't the only one headed for the Leader! Hydra swoops in and only chaos is on the menu.
description.35: What is the history of Miguel O' Hara, the new Spider-Man of 2099? Discover his backstory in this shocking issue! Plus, a rude interruption from agents of the future, the Public Eye squad!
description.36: Loki has possessed Odin's body, causing confusion and mayhem as Asgard's finest struggle to find answers!
description.37: Doctor Strange guest-stars in Thor's battle against Bloodaxe! Heimdall is returned to his normal state.
description.40: Johnny is ambushed by a cabal of cosmic villains out for revenge against the FF! Devos the Devastator, Paibok the Power Skrull, and...Johnny's Skrull wife, Lyja!?
description.42: Has Wolverine lost Silver Fox for a second time? Who can survive the sins of Weapon X?
description.46:
CABLE IS BACK! AND HE'S GOT JUST 24 HOURS TO WIPE THE AVENGERS FROM THE PAGES OF HISTORY!
How has Cable been reborn? Where has he been since "Second Coming"? And what dark event has driven him to destroy the Avengers? The answers are just the tip of an iceberg that threatens to smash the Marvel Universe to smithereens!
A crucial new series by the creators behind SUPERMAN/BATMAN and HULK, Jeph Loeb and Ed McGuinness
THE COUNTDOWN TO 2012's STATUS QUO-SHATTERING EPIC BEGINS HERE!
description.53: Matt Murdock saves Yves Chapoteau from the strong arm of the law. The Nameless One emerges.
description.54: Jamie Braddock has made his move, and victory is within his grasp! Only one person stands between him and total triumph: the amnesiac Meggan!
description.55: Alchemy: kidnapped! Trolls have abducted the young mutant, and only Excalibur can save him! But they'll need help to do it, so it's time to team up with the Uncanny X-Men!
description.56: Marlo Chandler is dead! Rick Jones seeks aid from Doctor Strange, Reed Richards, and Henry Pym to save the woman he loves. Is there any chance for Marlo? Meanwhile, Hulk shakes his fists at Agamemnon for striking a deal with his nemesis, the incorrigible Leader!
description.59: New York, 2099. Five teens cruise the skies above the city in their Whisper 3000 hovercar. But in this future society, the people still need a Spider-Man. Introducing Spidey 2099. Cooler tech, bigger baddies.
description.60: How can Eric and Balder save Sif from Mephisto when she doesn't want to be saved? Will Thor II remain powerless by Odin's grasp?
description.61: The Warriors Three commit treason - against Odin!
description.62: Spidey and Moon Knight join forces to stop the Hobgoblin's mercenary reign of terror!
description.65: The final confrontation of the Infinity War! Magus has the Infinity Gauntlet, and with it unlimited power! Do the FF and Earth's heroes even have a chance of stopping this invincible threat?
description.66: Someone continues to torment the members of Weapon X still living. So why is Maverick this tormentor's bodyguard?
description.69: Ghost Rider and the Nine have their final battle against Lilith!
description.72: Infinity War tie-in!  Moon Knight's condition worsens and not even the brilliant minds of Mister Fantastic or Doctor Strange can cure him without a sample.  So Moon Knight sets out to hunt Demogoblin for the key to his cure!
description.77: The Nightstalkers emerge! Blade joins Doctor Strange and Ghost Rider to combat growing vampiric evils. Lilith feels Blade's wrath first.
description.79: Just as John decides he wants to quit his mystical involvement with the Spirit of Vengeance, Hag and Troll cross his and Ghost Rider's path!
description.80: Jen attempts to save those turned into stone, by using a lesson in brain-switching to "trade places" with Weezi.
description.81: Large killer robots! Robotic Spiders! Spider-Slayers! The web-slinger must fight off robots of all different kinds and get to the bottom of who is behind these attacks!
description.82: The Spider-Slayers are loose! While touring Empire State University with his parents, Peter catches wind of an attack by Electro. Spider-Man must swing into action against Electro and a gaggle of homicidal robots! Plus, what's Black Cat up to?
description.83: The Gatherers arrive in Wakanda to kill the Black Panther, but the Avengers are hot on their tail to stop them.
description.84: Captain America and Falcon determine that Diamondback is held captive by Crossbones in the Rocky Mountains. Find out the fate of Rachel Leighton as Captain America faces the Skeleton Crew!
description.86: CAPTAIN AMERICA IS DEAD! The nation grieves the death of their hero while the Punisher continues his mission. And someone makes a surprise return…
description.87: Wolverine is infected! When nanotech machinery threatens to separate the adamantium from Wolverine’s cells, how will the mutant survive?
description.94: Who are the Gatherers and why do they seek to destroy the Black Panther? Plus, Sersi and Black Knight start a relationship...much to Crystal's dismay.
description.96: Left behind on'Byss,'Luke'travels with the newly-powerful'Emperor'Palpatine'to capture his sister'Leia. Meanwhile, the Jedi'Holocron'delivers a thousand-year-old prophecy to Leia, which tells of her battle against the young Emperor!

0.text: The Tribunal, alongside Eternity, retells the origins of each member of the Infinity Watch. And judgment is passed. Which members will be deemed worthy of Infinity Gems? The select few will shock you!

1.text: Blue Marvel is stepping on Quasar’s toes…by usurping his role as Protector of the Universe! Will Blue Marvel also become an Avenger? Captain Marvel stares death in the face. Luckily teammates Thor, Hercules, and Black Knight have her back!

2.text: Captain Zero has started a new chapter in his life... but all Spider-Man can remember are Zero’s days as a patient in the Pleasant Valley Mental Hospital.

3.text: Spider-Man joins Johnny Blaze and Ghost Rider's battle against Hag, Troll and Deathspawn, in an all-out Midtown Melee!

4.text: The X-Men, X-Force and X-Factor team up!

6.text: Agent Fury takes on Baron von Strucker of none other than Hydra!

10.text: Clea removes Umar and Baron Mordo, which releases Dormammu. To avoid demolition, Strange recruits Vishanti for a 5000 year-long war!

12.text: Punisher always seems to make enemies with one gang or another. This time, V.I.G.I.L. will fill that slot quite nicely.

13.text: Frank Castle, the scourge of the underworld known as the Punisher, must team-up with super-spy the Black Widow to stop a madman from unleashing Armageddon on the world.

15.text: Trapped in a horrific desert conflict, has Namorita finally gone too far?!

16.text: Gideon, X-Force’s greatest foe, challenges Night Thrasher!

17.text: The Redeemers encounter Modred the Mystic! Will he prove an ally to their cause?

18.text: The X-Men have to battle Sentinels, giant robots that don't take prisoners!

24.text: Cage is in over his head when a client distorts the truth behind a case. Enter the Rhino, a villain as impenetrable as Cage!

25.text: In the 31st century, Rancor battles the infamous Doom!

26.text: Down in the New York City sewers, Ghost Rider, Johnny Blaze and Venom must work together to find out where Spider-Man has been taken!

27.text: Switching bodies with Weezi proves perilous for She-Hulk!

28.text: It's trial day, and VENOM is called to the stand! When the symbiotic psycho hijacks a courtroom, it's up to Spider-Man and Daredevil to stop him! But can they do it before Venom declares everyone guilty?

32.text: Captain Britain, Meggan and Kitty are in Wakanda!

34.text: Iron Man (a.k.a. James Rhodes) vs. Atom Smasher, the atomic threat - with the stakes no less than nuclear Armageddon should our hero fail! Plus: Tony Stark confronts the secrets of his past, and Rhodey gets a new love interest in Rae LaCoste!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #287)

38.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 6. The machinations of some of the deadliest X-enemies are revealed, and members of multiple X-teams face down the Mutant Liberation Front.

41.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 5. The mystery surrounding the attempt on Xavier's life unravels as Apocalypse plans his next move.

42.text: Has Wolverine lost Silver Fox for a second time? Who can survive the sins of Weapon X?

45.text: After crash-landing their stolen Imperial ship, Luke and his new-found companion Tanith Shire are captured and enslaved by the Serpent Masters of Tanith's home planet. Artoo and Threepio are out of commission and the Millennium Falcon is light-years away, leaving Luke to find his own means of escape, with nothing but his wit, his skill, and his trusty lightsaber at hand!

46.text:
CABLE IS BACK! AND HE'S GOT JUST 24 HOURS TO WIPE THE AVENGERS FROM THE PAGES OF HISTORY!
How has Cable been reborn? Where has he been since "Second Coming"? And what dark event has driven him to destroy the Avengers? The answers are just the tip of an iceberg that threatens to smash the Marvel Universe to smithereens!

Cable and Kane set up a trap for Stryfe in Japan. But little do they know that Stryfe is doing exactly the same thing to them...

47.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 4. Our mutant heroes must not only contend with the forces of evil, but also with themselves!

49.text: Magus triumphant!  Who will win the Infinity War...and at what price?
Magus triumphant!  Who will win the Infinity War...and at what price?

50.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 1.  The X-Men are assaulted by the Horsemen of Apocalypse! Meanwhile, a deadly assassin aims his sights at Professor X!

51.text: X-CUTIONER'S SONG Part 3. Apocalypse awakens! The X-Men organize into two teams in order to rescue Cyclops and Jean Grey and locate X-Force.

52.text: When Luke's spy mission in Imperial territory turns out to be a trap set by none other than Darth Vader, his only hope for escape is a beautiful thief named Tanith Shire. Unfortunately, her only escape route leads straight out of the frying pan and into the fire!

57.text: Tony Stark is dead, and the Avengers want to know who the new Iron Man is! See Hawkeye, the Wasp, Dr. Pym and the Living Lightning show James Rhodes the ropes! Plus: the final fate of Kathy Dare, the woman who paralyzed Tony Stark with a bullet!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #286)

66.text: Someone continues to torment the members of Weapon X that are still living. So why is Maverick this tormentor's bodyguard?

69.text: Ghost Rider and the Nine have their final battle against Lilith!

70.text: The conclusion to "The Cold War of Nick Fury"!

71.text: What's better than a good ol' fashioned high speed car chase? Absolutely nothing!

73.text: It's the all-polluted, all-deadly FORCE OF NATURE vs. the New Warriors!

74.text: Night Thrasher battles a new foe, Tantrum!

75.text: Sam, Louise and Vicki are the Darkhold Redeemers! With the intent to save the world from an arcane evil, the crew tracks down a man who’s threatening to set off a bomb on a “fallen and lost” America!

76.text: Stories converge and explode in this jam-packed issue! Dakota North gets closer to finding Luke’s father…but is someone else tracking the same man? Meanwhile, Cage and the West Coast Avengers divert the disaster of the Power Man serum contaminating a local water supply!

77.text: The Nightstalkers emerge! Blade joins Doctor Strange and Ghost Rider to combat growing vampiric evils. Lilith feels Blade's wrath first.

78.text: A rift is caused between the Guardians of the Galaxy in the wake of an impending Badoon attack!

79.text: Just as John decides he wants to quit his mystical involvement with the Spirit of Vengeance, Hag and Troll cross his and Ghost Rider's path!

80.text: Jen attempts to save those turned into stone, by using a lesson in brain-switching to "trade places" with Weezi.

85.text: Based on the hit TV series! Don't miss the explosive first issue!

92.text: Doctor Strange comes face-to-face against his Masked self from Counter Earth! Then Magus’ machinations come into play!

95.text: In this issue, Luke volunteers for an espionage mission aboard Darth Vader's new battleship, but can he trust the Imperial Admiral he meets there, who claims to be helping the Rebels?

98.text: Delve into the history of Cable! Who is the man behind the mask of Stryfe?

99.text: The Magus is now in possession of a fully functioning Infinity Gauntlet.  What chance do Adam Warlock and the Marvel heroes have now?
